## 3. BattleStream Communication Protocol

### Writing TO Showdown (Input Commands)

All commands are prefixed with `>`:

| Command | Format | Purpose |
|---------|--------|---------|
| Start | `>start {"format":"[YourAddon] Singles"}` | Initialize battle |
| Add Player | `>player p1 {"name":"Ash","team":"<packed>"}` | Register player with packed team |
| Move | `>p1 move thunderbolt` or `>p1 move 2` | Use a move (by name or 1-based index) |
| Move + Target | `>p1 move 1 2` | Move with target (doubles: positive=foe, negative=ally) |
| Move + Mega | `>p1 move 1 mega` | Move with mega evolution |
| Switch | `>p1 switch 3` | Switch to party slot (1-based) |
| Multi-action | `>p1 move 1 2, switch 3` | Doubles: action per active slot, comma-separated |
| Pass | `>p1 pass` | Skip action (used in force-switch when slot doesn't need action) |
| Bag Item | `>p1 bag-item potion 1` | Use bag item on target slot |
| Used Ball | `>p1 used-ball` | Signal Poke Ball usage |
| Force Tie | `>forcetie` | End battle as tie (used for "Run") |
| Force Forme | `>forceforme p1a\|Species\|details\|hp/maxhp\|source` | In-battle evolution |

### Reading FROM Showdown (Output Messages)

Output is `type\npayload`:

**`update`** — Public battle log. Contains lines like:
```
update
|move|p1a: Pikachu|Thunderbolt|p2a: Squirtle
|-supereffective|p2a: Squirtle
|-damage|p2a: Squirtle|45/100
|
```

**`sideupdate`** — Private per-side data:
```
sideupdate
p1
|request|{"active":[...],"side":{"pokemon":[...]},"rqid":3}
```

**`end`** — Battle finished:
```
end
{"winner":"p1","turns":12,"p1":"Ash","p2":"Gary",...}
```

### Split Messages (Private vs Public HP)

Some messages use `|split|pN` to separate private (exact HP) from public (percentage):
```
|split|p1
|-damage|p1a: Pikachu|Pokemon Specific: 89/267
|-damage|p1a: Pikachu|33/100
```
Use the private line for the owning player, public for others.

