## 6. Team Packing — Pokemon Data to Showdown Format

Map your Pokemon data model to `PokemonSet`:

| Your Pokemon Field | Showdown Field | Notes |
|--------------------|----------------|-------|
| Unique ID | `uuid` | Custom field for tracking |
| Nickname | `name` | Display name |
| Species identifier | `species` | Lowercase species name (e.g. "pikachu") |
| Held item | `item` | Lowercase no-spaces (e.g. "leftovers") |
| Ability | `ability` | Ability name |
| Move names | `moves` | Array of move names |
| Move PP data | `movesInfo` | Array of `{maxPp, pp}` — custom field |
| Nature | `nature` | Nature name (e.g. "Adamant") |
| Gender | `gender` | `'M'`, `'F'`, or `''` |
| IVs per stat | `ivs` | `{hp, atk, def, spa, spd, spe}` |
| EVs per stat | `evs` | `{hp, atk, def, spa, spd, spe}` |
| Level | `level` | 1-100 |
| Shiny | `shiny` | Boolean |
| Happiness | `happiness` | 0-255 |
| Current HP | `currentHealth` | Custom field — actual HP (not max) |
| Caught-in ball | `pokeball` | Ball type |

For wild Pokemon without a full model: construct `PokemonSet` from the entity's dynamic properties (level, IVs, EVs, moves, ability, nature, gender).

