## 7. Actor System Design

Design an actor hierarchy:

### Base Actor
- Holds reference to battle, stream, and showdown side ID (`p1`, `p2`)
- Abstract methods: `packTeam()`, `receiveRequest()`, `onBattleEnd()`, `displayLog()`
- Tracks Pokemon info per battle position (e.g. `p1a`, `p1b` for doubles)

### Player Actor
- Wraps a Minecraft `Player` entity
- `receiveRequest()` → show ActionForm UI with move/switch/bag/run buttons
- `onBattleEnd()` → process EXP, EVs, level-ups, show summary
- Manages party tracking (which Pokemon participated, for EXP sharing)
- Handles Poke Ball catching flow (in wild battles)
- Registers post-battle callbacks when Pokemon are KO'd (for delayed EXP/EV processing)

### Wild Pokemon Actor
- Wraps a wild Pokemon entity
- Uses `RandomPlayerAI` for move selection
- `receiveRequest()` → AI chooses, delayed write to stream (2-4s)
- `onBattleEnd()` → despawn entity, drop items if applicable

### Trainer Actor
- Wraps a trainer NPC entity
- Uses `RandomPlayerAI` (easy) or heuristic AI (hard) based on difficulty
- Has a pre-defined party from trainer data
- `onBattleEnd()` → award money/items, handle win/loss scenarios

### Spectator Actor (optional)
- Players watching the battle
- Receives log display updates but sends no commands

