## 8. Player UI Flow (Minecraft Forms)

### Main Action Screen (ActionForm)
For each active Pokemon slot, show:
1. **Move buttons** — One per known move. Show: name, type icon, PP remaining/max, power, accuracy. Disabled if no PP or blocked.
2. **Bag button** — Opens bag submenu (healing items, PP restore, Poke Balls in wild). Disabled if bag not allowed.
3. **Switch button** — Opens party list of non-active, non-fainted Pokemon. Disabled if trapped or not allowed.
4. **Run button** — Ends battle as tie. Disabled if not allowed (trainer battles).
5. **Mega Evolution toggle** — If player has mega item and Pokemon has mega stone. Can only mega once per battle.

### Move Target Selection (Doubles/Triples)
After selecting a move, if targeting is needed, show target selection form based on `MoveTarget`:
- `adjacentFoe` — choose which opponent
- `adjacentAllyOrSelf` — choose ally or self
- `allAdjacentFoes`, `all`, `self` — auto-target, no form needed

### Bag Screen
Categories of usable items from player inventory:
- Healing (Potions, Berries) → use on active Pokemon
- PP Restore (Leppa Berry, Elixir) → select which move to restore
- Revives → select which fainted party member
- Poke Balls (wild only) → triggers catch sequence

### Switch Screen
List non-active party Pokemon. Skip fainted unless force-switch. Show species, level, HP, status.

### Force Switch
When a Pokemon faints or is forced out, show switch screen with no back button. Player MUST pick.

### Wait Screen
Between turns, show battle log (last ~6 messages), current turn, weather/terrain. Subtitle "..." to indicate waiting.

